OL,3,CInquest into death of girl at water
OL,4,Cpark questions training for lifeguards
OL,6,FThe inquest also heard from the water
OL,7,Fpark's director, Stuart Marston, has
OL,8,Fbeen giving evidence and admitted
OL,9,Fthere was a sign that warned of
OL,10,F"danger, shallow water" which was
OL,11,Fbrought in after a previous incident
OL,12,Fwhere someone hit the bottom after
OL,13,Fjumping in.
OL,15,FHowever, there was not a sign warning
OL,16,Fthat, although the edge of the water
OL,17,Fwas shallow, parts of it sharply
OL,18,Fdropped away to 4.5 metres, so parents
OL,19,Fwould not necessarily know of the
OL,20,Fdanger of the deep water.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@WO]
